For the Import of the Queſtion, Is it Peace? or, Is it well, Jehu? as it might be rendred, and is ſo in other Verſes; it is as

if he ſhould have ſaid,
Is there no bad News, Jehu, that occaſions thy unexpected coming? What means this thy ſudden and haſty Journey? Is the Army routed by the Syrians? Is Hamath recovered again? Is it Peace? Is there any new Rebellion or Conſpiracy? What ill Tidings doſt thou bring? Is it Peace, Jehu?  There needed no ſtay for an Anſwer, the very Countenance of Jehu doubtleſs ſpoke Death to Joram; and his Tongue ſeconds it in the following Anſwer of the Text, viz.
